    <item>
      <title>Daily Security News from @trustpath - Apr 21, 2017</title>
      <link>//crypt0.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2017-04-21/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Apr 2017 18:05:01 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>//crypt0.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2017-04-21/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Daily Security news from &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/trustpath&#34;&gt;@trustpath&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Four steps to keeping client data safe from cyber fraud&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cybercrime and data breaches have long been associated with banks and other large institutions, rather than advisers. Criminal gangs are, however, &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.professionaladviser.com/professional-adviser/opinion/3008740/four-steps-to-keeping-client-data-safe-from-cyber-fraud&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.professionaladviser.com/professional-adviser/opinion/3008740/four-steps-to-keeping-client-data-safe-from-cyber-fraud&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Recent Decisions Shine Light on Employer Liability for Data Breaches of&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lexology (registration) In both cases, which involved large-scale data breaches affecting thousands of employees, the courts absolved the employers of any potential liability &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.lexology.com/library/detail.aspx?g=5662322c-711e-4298-b1f3-55bfbc1c51d3&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.lexology.com/library/detail.aspx?g=5662322c-711e-4298-b1f3-55bfbc1c51d3&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;How Revel Protects Your Restaurant Against Data Breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;security. Data breaches has become one of the greatest threats to a &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://revelsystems.com/blog/2017/04/20/how-revel-protects-your-restaurant-against-data-breaches/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://revelsystems.com/blog/2017/04/20/how-revel-protects-your-restaurant-against-data-breaches/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Breach Notification Update: New Mexico becomes the 48th State Requiring&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JD Supra (press release) As the frequency of data breaches continues, so do legislative developments on notification requirements that must be met in the event of a breach of &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/breach-notification-update-new-mexico-58508/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/breach-notification-update-new-mexico-58508/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;CISO&amp;rsquo;s fail to keep pace with data breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ServiceNow commissioned Oxford Economics to survey 300 CISOs and found that more than 80% believe data breaches in their company are going &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.cbronline.com/news/cybersecurity/breaches/cisos-fail-keep-pace-data-breaches/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.cbronline.com/news/cybersecurity/breaches/cisos-fail-keep-pace-data-breaches/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Data Privacy and Security Legal Reform, and Plaintiffs&amp;rsquo; Bar White Paper the&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JD Supra (press release) &amp;hellip; particularly in recent cases that seem to impose strict liability on companies following data breaches. Madison spoke as in house privacy counsel for &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/data-privacy-and-security-legal-reform-41246/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/data-privacy-and-security-legal-reform-41246/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Governments worldwide allocate funds to fight cybercrime&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Massive data breaches, fraud and identity schemes, violent crimes, trafficking and international terrorism are all linked to and aided by the increase in &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://exclusive.multibriefs.com/content/governments-worldwide-allocate-funds-to-fight-cybercrime/science-technology&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://exclusive.multibriefs.com/content/governments-worldwide-allocate-funds-to-fight-cybercrime/science-technology&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;A clean bill of health for data security&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether a result of insider negligence (the leading cause of data breaches), unencrypted medical devices, the absence of bring-your-own-device &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://gcn.com/articles/2017/04/21/health-data-security.aspx&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://gcn.com/articles/2017/04/21/health-data-security.aspx&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;LogicHub strives to automate threat-hunting for security ops teams&lt;/h3&gt;
